external_knowledge:
Chief critic refers to the user with reviewer_id = 0;
Unique identifiers for books are referenced as book_id;
The genre of the book is a categorical description of the type of book such as fiction, non-fiction, etc.

- 'those who pen the tales themselves' refers to users with the role 'Author';
- 'language of the first light' symbolizes the primary language identified by language_id 1;
- 'whispers of critique' metaphorically refers to review titles and descriptions;
- 'tales' are represented by the book names.

- 'prolific writers' refers to authors who have written more than one book;
- The primary language is the language in which the author predominantly writes;
- 'main authors' are those who have a 'main author' designation in the database.
